content.description: Starts in a shallow and sometimes wet dihedral.  Climbs past some moss and other flora to an easy finish.
content.protection: 3 bolts to a 2-bolt anchor with chains.
content.location: 20 feet left of "Hack in the Fast Lane"

content.description: Stand on a boulder and clip the low first bolt. Climb the crux moves over the bulge, and then up easier but sustained 5.9 and 5.10a moves to the anchor.

Start as for Ferntasm, but head left to the first bolt.  Climb the slightly overhanging face past two more bolts to a great hold about 2/3 of the way up.  There are plentiful and interesting (albeit small) holds all of the way to the anchors.  Watch for the runout between the last bolt and the anchors.
content.protection: Three bolts to a two bolt anchor shared with Ferntasm.
content.location: The line of bolts immediate left of the Ferntasm dihedral.

content.description: Starts to the right of "8 It Grand" under a bulge. Pulling the bulge is the crux.
Climb the face just left of the water streak through easy pockets to a long deadpoint that marks the beginning of the crux.
content.location: Two routes right of "the smoking lounge"  which is a cave about 9 feet tall and deep enough for two people who really like each other to hang out.

content.description: Small holds lead over the bulging start and past the first bolt and then give way to easier climbing.
content.protection: 3 bolts to a 2 bolt anchor with chains.

content.description: Starts right of large tree near the wall. A bit spicy at the bottom and a bit confusing at the top. Runout to bolt 2.
Start on the tufa, and move up to the bulging dihedral.
Starts on ledge with strange underclings. Work your way up on crimps. Shares anchors with "Ferntasm" and "Left of Ferntasm."
content.location: Look for large, broken Oak tree near wall. "George of the Jungle" is to the right of the tree. "Ferntasm", "Left of Ferntasm" and "Ferntasm Twice Removed" are left of the tree in that order.

content.description: Climb the dihedral behind the tree past two bolts to the anchors.  There is a great flake near the second bolt that is very positive and provides a good rest.  There is a healthy runout between the first and second bolts.
content.protection: Two or three bolts to a shared anchor.
content.location:
Ferntasm is located left of George of the Jungle and Left of Ferntasm is left of Ferntasm. 

  Climbs a dihedral on the left side of the wall, immediately behind a very large tree.  There are additional climbs on both sides that lead to the same anchor.

content.description: Just left of Arborcidal Tendencies. Climbs the water streak. Originally rated 5.11b, but is significantly harder than the route to the right. Perhaps holds have broken.
The first bolt for this route is a little high, but climbing is mellow down low.  This route works left after the first bolt through good, fun holds.  Very good route on high quality limestone.
content.protection: 2 bolts, high first bolt.  Chain anchors
content.location:
Cliptomania is located between Arborcidal Tendencies and Mrs Johnson. 

  Climbs the blue streak on the far right side of Arbor Wall, near a large flat rock.

content.description: This variation of Cliptomania keeps hands right of the boltline for a more challenging route that feels significantly different from Cliptomania.
content.location: Same bolts as Cliptomania but stay to the right.

content.description: Climb to the top of the small cave referred to as the "smoking lounge" and continue onto the face to the chains
content.location: starts on the right side of the smoking lounge.

content.description: The most difficult route at this section or Arbor wall.  Climb up through nice pockets on the left side of the small cave ("the Smoking Lounge") and then continue straight up the face.  The crux lies between the last bolt and the anchors as the holds disappear.
content.location: just left of "the smoking lounge" cave.

content.description: A direct line to the Arbortrary anchors. This is a bit harder, going over a slight bulge at the bottom.
content.protection: Set up a rope on Arbortrary anchors.
content.location: Just left of the Arbortrary start.

climbs.name: Arbortrary
climbs.fa: Jan Salinas, Josh Dossett, Dave Phillips

content.description: Crux is between bolt 2 & 3.  It can be wet after a good rain.
content.location: Route located just left of Smoking Lounge and Burning Bush

content.description: This variation of Juniper starts on the water streak to the right of Juniper and eventually joins back up with the original line.
content.location: Starts just right of Juniper. Same bolts.

content.description: From the top of the boulder, step up across the 3-foot gap between the boulder and the wall. Use pockets, crimper holds, side-pulls, and a sloper. Crux is between second and third bolts, where some go left and some straight up.
content.location: Arbor Wall, left of Cliptomania. Start on top of a 10-foot long, flat-topped, 4-foot high boulder.

content.description: Traverses up and to the right through a series of large huecos, slots and ledges. Anchors are on the right of a small arete at the top of the cliff.

Arbor Wall is located on the left (Dead Cats) side of Reimer's, and is the first major wall past Dead Cats and Rhetoric Walls.  A large oak tree keeps much of the wall in the shade, making it a good choice on summer afternoons when the rest of Reimer's is roasting in the mid-day sun.  There are about nine routes on Arbor Wall, all in the 5.10 to 5.11 range.  On the right side of the wall is a limestone "flow" (a steep gully carved by an old stream) that provides a quick scramble to the top of the cliff, and an alternate way back to the parking lot.
